===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|flok||tuft of wool|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|floc||tuft of wool|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|floccus||tuft of wool|lang=la}}, probably from {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*flokko||down, wool, flock}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*flukkōn-}}, {{m|gem-pro|*flukkan-}}, {{m|gem-pro|*fluksōn-||down, flock}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*plAwək-||hair, fibres, tuft}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|flocko||down|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|dum|-}} {{term|vlocke||flock|lang=dum}}, {{etyl|no|-}} dialectal {{term|flugsa||snowflake|lang=no}}. Other cognate Albanian {{term|flokë||hair|lang=sq}}.

